<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 19. Gastrocentrum gaoligongense sp. nov. Holotype male. A aedeagus in ventral view B. tegmen in lateral view b apex of tegmen in lateral view C tegmen in ventral view D phallus in ventral view d apex of phallus E spicular fork F pygidium G sixth ventrite H antenna. Scale bars: 1 mm." , "Figure 10. Drawing of elytral asetiferous punctations. A Gastrocentrum magnum sp. nov. B G. dux C G. regulare sp. nov. D G. xiaodongi sp. nov. E G. gaoligongense sp. nov. F-H G. zayuense sp. nov. The numbers 1 - 10 annotate the serial rows of primary asetiferous punctuations (PAP). Abbreviations: a accessory asetiferous punctations." , "Figure 22. A, B Isocymatodera atricolor. C, D I. kolbei. E Gastrocentrum gaoligongense. Abbreviations: cov common oviduct ovp ovipositor sp spermatheca spg spermathecal gland spgtt top tail of spermathecal gland spglt lateral tail of spermathecal gland va vagina vs vaginal sclerite. Scale bar: 1 mm." , "Figure 25. Geographical distribution map of the genus Gastrocentrum." , "Figures 1 - 9. Habitus. 1 Gastrocentrum magnum sp. nov. Holotype 2 G. dux from Australia 3 G. unicolor (Lectotype of G. pauper) 4 G. regulare sp. nov. Holotype 5 G. xiaodongi sp. nov. Holotype 6 G. zayuense sp. nov. Holotype 7 G. gaoligongense sp. nov. Holotype 8 Tillus nitidus comb. nov. Holotype 9 Isocymatodera atricolor Syntype. Scale bars: 5 mm (1, 2) 2 mm (3 - 9)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467732" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467718" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467729" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467727" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467717" .

